 <label>Figure 7.</label>
 <caption>
  <title>Lifetime of the RQS state.</title>
  <p>This schematic diagram based on 
   <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig5">Figure 5A</xref> defines the ‘boundaries’ of the transient RQS 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf232">
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>q</mi>
       <mrow>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mo>⁢</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>⁢</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>⁢</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
       <mi>τ</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> (red line) and 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf233">
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>q</mi>
       <mrow>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo>⁢</mo>
        <mi>p</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>⁢</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
       <mi>τ</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> (blue line). 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf234">
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>q</mi>
       <mrow>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mo>⁢</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>⁢</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>⁢</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
       <mi>τ</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> gives the value of 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf235">
     <mi>q</mi>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> for which the average time to extinction is equal to 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf236">
     <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
      <mrow>
       <mi>τ</mi>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> is defined similarly but for the speciation process. Average times to speciation and extinction become equal at the critical value 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf237">
     <msub>
      <mi>q</mi>
      <mi>c</mi>
     </msub>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> at which RQS persists the longest. For 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf238">
     <mrow>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mo>=</mo>
      <mn>50</mn>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>, 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf239">
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>q</mi>
       <mi>c</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo>≈</mo>
      <mn>2.4</mn>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> and this value, along with the RQS lifetime, increases with 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="inf240">
     <mi>d</mi>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>.
  </p>
